WEBVTT

00:14.182 --> 00:16.884
(rushing waters)

00:25.359 --> 00:28.362
(slow gentle music)

00:30.030 --> 00:32.700
(woman humming)

00:42.843 --> 00:46.480
* My love

00:46.480 --> 00:50.384
* Is alone

00:50.384 --> 00:55.356
* With you

00:58.726 --> 01:02.396
* So you wait in that sea

01:02.396 --> 01:05.433
* Caught up and free

01:13.207 --> 01:15.008
* With me

01:15.008 --> 01:17.678
* And I dream

01:17.678 --> 01:21.682
* Nothing's what
it seems to be *

01:27.788 --> 01:31.859
* I love

01:31.892 --> 01:35.563
* Is alone

01:35.563 --> 01:37.765
* With you

01:44.605 --> 01:47.241
(ominous music)

01:55.816 --> 01:58.619
(heavy breathing)

02:11.232 --> 02:12.065
(dramatic music)
(water splashes)

02:12.065 --> 02:14.402
(Liz gasps)

02:19.673 --> 02:20.841
- [Liz] Brody.

02:28.649 --> 02:31.319
(ominous music)

02:38.091 --> 02:40.928
(coffee bubbling)

03:03.684 --> 03:06.186
(tense music)

03:14.528 --> 03:15.796
- [Payton] Stop!

03:15.829 --> 03:16.864
Stop, please!

03:16.864 --> 03:18.499
Someone help, please!

03:18.532 --> 03:20.033
Help me, please help!

03:20.033 --> 03:21.235
Hurry!

03:21.235 --> 03:25.038
Hurry Liz, don't!
(Liz sniffling)

03:25.038 --> 03:27.375
(Liz cries)

03:33.714 --> 03:34.548
(ominous music)

03:34.548 --> 03:37.385
(heavy breathing)

03:47.227 --> 03:49.997
- [Therapist] Were you able
to get any sleep this week?

03:51.732 --> 03:53.066
- A couple of hours, maybe.

03:54.702 --> 03:55.503
- The nightmare?

03:57.405 --> 04:00.073
- Getting progressively worse.

04:00.073 --> 04:01.742
I got taken under this time.

04:01.742 --> 04:02.576
- Oh no.

04:03.911 --> 04:05.212
Then?

04:05.245 --> 04:06.079
- Then I woke up.

04:08.516 --> 04:10.684
I have this feeling of dread,

04:10.684 --> 04:12.353
as if it's building
to something.

04:14.087 --> 04:15.055
- [Therapist] Yeah?

04:16.457 --> 04:18.959
- Sometimes I feel like I'm
gonna lose it completely.

04:21.595 --> 04:23.364
- I understand.

04:23.397 --> 04:27.267
Lack of sleep can be tough
on the mind and the body.

04:28.268 --> 04:29.370
You still certain you don't

04:29.403 --> 04:31.071
want to be prescribed
to anything?

04:31.071 --> 04:33.073
- I don't want anything, no.

04:33.106 --> 04:34.975
I'm almost more terrified
of what I'll see

04:34.975 --> 04:36.377
if I actually can't wake up.

04:38.479 --> 04:41.482
- [Therapist] How are the
meditation exercises going?

04:41.482 --> 04:43.551
- Well, I'm doing them.

04:44.452 --> 04:45.285
- That's good.

04:46.286 --> 04:47.120
- I guess.

04:51.124 --> 04:52.159
It's been a year now.

04:54.227 --> 04:55.262
- [Therapist] A year?

04:56.430 --> 04:57.498
- Since the attack.

04:58.966 --> 05:01.101
- Yes, of course.

05:03.804 --> 05:05.606
How do you feel about that?

05:05.639 --> 05:06.807
- Shitty, obviously.

05:07.975 --> 05:08.809
- Right.

05:10.478 --> 05:11.311
- Alone.

05:15.282 --> 05:16.950
- Do you still blame yourself?

05:18.986 --> 05:21.489
(tense music)

05:25.993 --> 05:28.662
(phone ringing)

05:31.665 --> 05:32.766
- Hey.

05:32.766 --> 05:34.602
- [Roberta] Hey, beautiful.

05:34.635 --> 05:36.136
How ya doing?

05:36.136 --> 05:40.541
- Oh, you know, tired, headache.

05:40.541 --> 05:41.375
The usual.

05:42.543 --> 05:44.311
- [Roberta] How
was your session?

05:44.344 --> 05:45.679
- Oh, swell.

05:46.514 --> 05:48.015
"How does that make you feel?

05:48.048 --> 05:51.284
"And how do you feel
about that?" all day.

05:51.318 --> 05:54.822
- [Roberta] And how do
you feel about that?

05:54.822 --> 05:56.390
- Shut up jerk face.

05:56.390 --> 05:57.958
- [Roberta] I am
not a jerk face.

05:57.991 --> 06:00.160
- You're a part-time jerk face.

06:00.160 --> 06:01.061
- [Roberta] Yeah?

06:01.061 --> 06:02.696
And the other part-time I'm a

06:02.696 --> 06:05.466
luscious, righteous,
goddess, right?

06:05.499 --> 06:06.333
- Right.

06:07.968 --> 06:09.970
How was your day luscious?

06:09.970 --> 06:12.640
- [Roberta] You know
me, I slay all day.

06:12.640 --> 06:15.342
- You did not just
say slay all day.

06:15.375 --> 06:16.577
- [Roberta] I did.

06:16.577 --> 06:17.911
- You didn't.

06:17.978 --> 06:18.846
- [Roberta] I did though.

06:18.879 --> 06:20.047
- I hate you.

06:20.047 --> 06:21.381
- [Roberta] You love me.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.016
- You suck!

06:23.016 --> 06:24.852
- [Roberta] Only if he let me.

06:24.885 --> 06:26.920
(Roberta laughs)

06:26.920 --> 06:29.923
Hey, let me take
you out tonight.

06:29.923 --> 06:31.592
Let's go do something fun.

06:31.659 --> 06:33.494
(Liz sighs)

06:33.527 --> 06:36.196
- I don't really feel
like going anywhere.

06:36.229 --> 06:38.198
I'm already lounging.

06:38.198 --> 06:40.901
- [Roberta] Ah, it's one of
those kinds of days, huh?

06:42.069 --> 06:43.704
- Pretty much.

06:43.737 --> 06:45.272
- [Roberta] Okay.

06:45.272 --> 06:49.076
Then let me come over
and make you dinner.

06:49.076 --> 06:51.545
- I certainly won't
argue against that.

06:51.579 --> 06:52.680
- [Roberta] Shocker!

06:54.414 --> 06:56.517
I'll be by around six.

06:57.417 --> 06:58.586
- Sounds good.

06:58.586 --> 07:00.387
- [Roberta] See
you then beautiful.

07:00.420 --> 07:02.389
- Bye, luscious goddess.

07:08.395 --> 07:11.064
(clock chiming)

07:29.049 --> 07:31.719
(ominous music)

07:49.970 --> 07:52.105
(Liz screams)
(dramatic music)

07:52.105 --> 07:54.942
(heavy breathing)

08:12.760 --> 08:14.461
- [Roberta] So.

08:14.494 --> 08:15.328
- So.

08:16.263 --> 08:17.497
- What do you think?

08:17.497 --> 08:19.466
- It was a'ight.

08:19.499 --> 08:20.634
- I'll do better next time.

08:20.634 --> 08:22.269
- Could you please?

08:22.269 --> 08:23.170
- Okay.

08:23.170 --> 08:25.639
- It was amazing, thank you.

08:28.141 --> 08:28.976
- My pleasure.

08:30.944 --> 08:32.212
- Oh no, I'll do that.

08:32.212 --> 08:34.314
- Nada, I got this.

08:34.347 --> 08:35.182
You chillax.

08:38.652 --> 08:41.321
(water running)

08:41.354 --> 08:43.691
Hey, wanna watch a movie?

08:43.691 --> 08:45.192
- Maybe, what are you thinking?

08:46.526 --> 08:48.696
- I don't know, something funny.

08:49.630 --> 08:51.131
Got us a little party favor.

08:51.131 --> 08:52.299
- Ah.

08:52.332 --> 08:53.734
(Liz chuckles)

08:53.734 --> 08:55.569
You know I'm not down
on the devils lettuce.

08:55.636 --> 08:57.971
- Still scared of
the reefer madness?

08:58.005 --> 09:00.841
- I'm terrified of those
herbal jazz cigarettes.

09:00.874 --> 09:02.810
- Oh, come on, it's
just ganja, babe.

09:04.011 --> 09:05.545
I keep telling you this
will help you sleep.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.547
- I know, but-

09:07.547 --> 09:09.583
- [Roberta] How are you
sleeping by the way?

09:09.650 --> 09:10.417
Any better?

09:11.852 --> 09:13.721
- Not really.

09:13.721 --> 09:16.990
I managed maybe a couple
of shitty hours a night.

09:18.491 --> 09:19.392
- Oh babe.

09:21.361 --> 09:24.031
I'm so sorry, that really sucks.

09:26.734 --> 09:29.737
You know, what's great
to help you sleep?

09:29.737 --> 09:31.605
Keep all the bad dreams away?

09:31.672 --> 09:32.439
- What's that?

09:32.439 --> 09:34.842
(Liz laughs)

09:38.045 --> 09:39.713
- Making sweet love by the fire.

09:41.248 --> 09:42.950
- My fireplace is broken.

09:45.719 --> 09:48.388
Making sweet love will
keep the sharks away?

09:48.388 --> 09:50.724
- Oh yeah, they hate the sound.

09:50.758 --> 09:53.460
(women giggling)

09:58.231 --> 09:59.266
- I'm sorry.

10:01.101 --> 10:01.935
I can't.

10:01.935 --> 10:02.970
I don't know.

10:05.072 --> 10:05.906
- It's okay.

10:06.907 --> 10:07.708
I understand.

10:12.646 --> 10:15.282
(Liz sighs)

10:15.282 --> 10:16.116
- Do you?

10:16.984 --> 10:17.818
- Of course.

10:20.053 --> 10:23.056
- I don't feel ready
to go there yet.

10:23.056 --> 10:24.257
- I know.

10:24.291 --> 10:25.292
I'm sorry, I didn't
mean to make you feel-

10:25.292 --> 10:27.227
- No, no, no, no
don't say sorry.

10:27.227 --> 10:31.098
You've been nothing but
amazing and patient with me.

10:31.131 --> 10:34.301
I don't know who would
put up with waiting-

10:34.301 --> 10:35.302
- Four months.

10:36.303 --> 10:37.270
- Has it been?

10:38.471 --> 10:39.673
- Yeah.

10:39.673 --> 10:41.241
Not that I noticed or anything.

10:42.776 --> 10:43.643
- Yeah right.

10:47.147 --> 10:50.117
- We can just cuddle
and watch a movie.

10:51.284 --> 10:52.085
- I'll take it.

10:54.755 --> 10:55.756
(slow gentle music)

10:55.756 --> 10:56.990
- I just wanna be here.

10:58.959 --> 11:00.093
- I'm glad you're here.

11:10.804 --> 11:13.473
(ominous music)

11:20.147 --> 11:22.983
(heavy breathing)

11:23.016 --> 11:23.884
Oh God, no.

11:37.164 --> 11:39.666
(tense music)

11:53.713 --> 11:56.416
(dramatic music)

11:57.918 --> 11:59.519
(Liz gasps)

11:59.552 --> 12:02.255
(heavy breathing)

12:04.491 --> 12:05.893
- Hey.

12:05.893 --> 12:07.060
Hey.

12:07.094 --> 12:07.928
Hey, it's okay.

12:09.362 --> 12:10.197
It's okay.

12:11.564 --> 12:12.499
- [Therapist] It
must be nice to have

12:12.499 --> 12:14.067
someone who supports you, yes?

12:14.067 --> 12:16.569
- Of course, it's great.

12:16.603 --> 12:17.604
Almost too great.

12:19.072 --> 12:20.573
- And what do you mean by that?

12:21.741 --> 12:25.512
- You know, just
too good to be true.

12:25.545 --> 12:27.214
- Ah, yes.

12:28.415 --> 12:32.119
- She's just so
loving and sweet.

12:32.119 --> 12:34.221
I feel like a total
asshole by comparison.

12:37.024 --> 12:39.359
- Well, when you're
going through something,

12:39.359 --> 12:41.228
it sounds like she
understands that.

12:41.261 --> 12:42.095
- She does,

12:43.430 --> 12:47.935
but I'm always wary of
anyone who seems too perfect.

12:47.935 --> 12:51.471
You know, meanwhile, here
I am an emotional mess who

12:55.042 --> 12:57.710
can't even get
intimate with her.

12:57.710 --> 13:01.248
- Has she expressed any
feelings to you about that?

13:01.281 --> 13:04.952
- No, not really.

13:06.153 --> 13:08.121
I mean, she seems
disappointed at times,

13:08.121 --> 13:09.890
but who wouldn't, right?

13:15.062 --> 13:17.164
Every time we get close,

13:18.098 --> 13:19.099
I just can't.

13:21.401 --> 13:23.670
- [Therapist] Have you
been with women before?

13:24.604 --> 13:25.605
- Yeah.

13:25.638 --> 13:27.607
In college I dated both,

13:28.976 --> 13:32.913
but Seth was my first real
long-term relationship though.

13:36.483 --> 13:38.618
Why did you think I-

13:38.651 --> 13:41.321
- Oh, just asking.

13:41.321 --> 13:44.291
- Yeah, no, it's,
it's not that at all.

13:45.825 --> 13:46.860
It's more like,

13:48.095 --> 13:49.930
this wall I can't break through.

13:51.865 --> 13:55.602
Almost as if he won't let me.

13:57.470 --> 13:58.671
- Who?

13:58.671 --> 13:59.472
Seth?

14:00.440 --> 14:02.542
- Maybe, or,

14:03.676 --> 14:04.511
the shark?

14:06.846 --> 14:11.151
I don't know, that sounds
ridiculous and bat shit.

14:11.184 --> 14:14.988
- That does not sound
ridiculous and bat shit.

14:14.988 --> 14:16.957
It makes sense in a way.

14:16.957 --> 14:17.790
- It does?

14:19.226 --> 14:21.895
A shark not wanting
me to be intimate?

14:22.795 --> 14:23.663
- Why not?

14:24.998 --> 14:27.334
It doesn't want to lose
its power over you.

14:27.367 --> 14:30.037
If you let yourself go and
become intimate with someone,

14:30.037 --> 14:33.506
you may feel better, if you
feel better, you may relax,

14:33.540 --> 14:34.741
if you relax, you may-

14:34.741 --> 14:36.743
- I may not have
the dreams anymore.

14:36.809 --> 14:38.311
Right, right.

14:38.311 --> 14:40.013
- I'm just tossing ideas around.

14:41.148 --> 14:43.483
the human mind is very complex.

14:43.483 --> 14:44.985
- Isn't it though?

14:44.985 --> 14:47.988
I just want to be able to shut
it off and be able to sleep.

14:47.988 --> 14:49.822
- Well, have you been
doing the meditation?

14:49.856 --> 14:51.824
- The meditations, yes.

14:51.824 --> 14:53.326
I thought exercise
would help too,

14:53.326 --> 14:55.728
but I'm just so damn
tired all the time.

14:58.731 --> 15:01.068
- Have you given any
more thought to the pool?

15:02.235 --> 15:03.670
- No.

15:03.670 --> 15:05.338
No way, not ready for that.

15:07.040 --> 15:09.209
- [Therapist] Okay, no
problem, understood.

15:11.611 --> 15:14.581
- I'll get there, just not yet.

15:16.549 --> 15:17.384
- Understood.

15:19.953 --> 15:23.623
Is next week at eight
still good for you?

15:23.690 --> 15:25.625
- Yes, it should be.

15:25.625 --> 15:27.694
- I have an appointment
next Wednesday,

15:27.727 --> 15:29.062
if that works for you.

15:30.430 --> 15:33.466
My dog, Ryan has an appointment
on our usual Tuesday, so.

15:34.901 --> 15:37.070
- Your dog's name is Ryan?

15:37.104 --> 15:38.938
- Yeah, kinda funny, right?

15:38.938 --> 15:41.208
He was my brother's first,
(ominous music)

15:41.241 --> 15:42.709
so he came to me named.

15:42.709 --> 15:44.377
So I'll go ahead
and put you down.

15:48.748 --> 15:50.383
(Liz screams)

15:50.383 --> 15:51.818
Oh my God, are you okay?

15:51.818 --> 15:52.652
What happened?

15:52.719 --> 15:54.487
(heavy breathing)

15:54.487 --> 15:55.989
Okay, just breathe, breathe.

15:57.124 --> 15:59.292
Everything is fine.

15:59.292 --> 16:00.827
What did you see?

16:00.893 --> 16:01.728
- I,

16:03.663 --> 16:04.497
I can't.

16:05.832 --> 16:07.100
I can't.

16:07.134 --> 16:08.935
- Okay, okay, just
breathe and relax.

16:09.969 --> 16:10.803
- Whoa.

16:10.803 --> 16:12.772
I'm so sorry.

16:12.772 --> 16:14.007
- No, do not apologize.

16:14.007 --> 16:15.842
- This is really
embarrassing, I-

16:15.842 --> 16:17.077
- No, no, not now.

16:19.412 --> 16:20.847
- I should go.

16:22.482 --> 16:24.351
Apparently I'm seeing shit now.

16:24.351 --> 16:25.185
I

16:27.987 --> 16:30.690
saw a shark in the window.

16:38.031 --> 16:40.100
- You mean out there?

16:40.133 --> 16:41.501
- Yeah.

16:41.501 --> 16:43.002
It was swimming towards you,

16:43.002 --> 16:45.972
moving through the
air like water.

16:46.939 --> 16:47.774
Oh wow!

16:49.176 --> 16:51.111
I need to fucking
sleep, don't I?

16:56.516 --> 16:57.950
Am I going crazy?

16:58.951 --> 17:00.453
- No, you're not.

17:00.487 --> 17:03.723
Like I said, lack of sleep
can be brutal on the mind.

17:05.225 --> 17:07.360
I'm going to recommend
you to a colleague

17:07.360 --> 17:08.561
that can prescribe you some-

17:08.628 --> 17:09.462
- No!

17:11.364 --> 17:12.232
No pills.

17:14.734 --> 17:15.568
- Okay.

17:16.836 --> 17:18.205
I understand, no pills.

17:21.408 --> 17:24.077
(ominous music)

17:34.087 --> 17:35.088
- [Payton] Help!

17:35.088 --> 17:35.922
Help please!

17:35.922 --> 17:37.590
Someone help, please!

17:37.590 --> 17:39.192
Help me, please help!

17:39.226 --> 17:44.231
Hurry, hurry Liz, help!
(ominous music)

18:13.793 --> 18:16.696
(machine whirring)

18:31.077 --> 18:32.645
- Excuse me.

18:32.645 --> 18:33.480
Excuse me.

18:34.647 --> 18:35.482
Excuse me!

18:39.319 --> 18:40.253
It's Hector. Right?

18:42.289 --> 18:43.089
- Javier.

18:43.089 --> 18:44.591
- Javier, right.

18:44.591 --> 18:47.294
Hey look, Javier, I know
you're doing your job,

18:47.294 --> 18:50.563
but could you maybe do it later?

18:50.597 --> 18:52.299
Or better yet tomorrow

18:52.299 --> 18:54.066
or never?

18:55.635 --> 18:57.136
(Liz chuckles)

18:57.136 --> 18:59.439
It's just, I have a really bad
headache from lack of sleep

18:59.472 --> 19:01.308
and it's especially
bad right now.

19:02.309 --> 19:04.477
I would really appreciate it.

19:04.511 --> 19:06.179
I could maybe even
give you some money.

19:06.179 --> 19:07.079
- I can't do it.

19:07.113 --> 19:08.014
I have to finish.

19:08.014 --> 19:09.148
- Well, maybe, I don't know.

19:09.148 --> 19:11.451
You could use a rake.

19:11.484 --> 19:12.652
- [Javier] Huh?

19:12.652 --> 19:14.120
- You know, a rake.

19:14.153 --> 19:15.288
What you're supposed to use

19:15.288 --> 19:17.190
after you've gathered
up the leaves.

19:17.190 --> 19:19.592
- I can't do it, I no have.

19:19.626 --> 19:20.793
- You don't have a rake?

19:23.029 --> 19:24.864
So then what the...

19:24.864 --> 19:26.766
What are you even doing then?

19:26.799 --> 19:29.602
You're just blowing leaves in
dirt from one yard to another.

19:29.602 --> 19:31.338
You're not cleaning shit.

19:31.338 --> 19:32.672
You're just spreading
dirt everywhere

19:32.705 --> 19:34.874
and disturbing everyone's peace!

19:34.874 --> 19:36.276
And it helps nothing.

19:36.309 --> 19:37.477
Does it make you
feel good to know

19:37.510 --> 19:39.646
you are literally
doing nothing useful?

19:39.646 --> 19:41.681
Why don't you blow
the leaves into a pile

19:41.681 --> 19:43.616
and pick them the
fuck up and toss them?

19:43.650 --> 19:44.484
Why?
(tense music)

19:44.484 --> 19:45.318
Tell me why?

19:50.122 --> 19:52.492
- Sorry senora, I
have to finish work.

19:56.195 --> 19:58.365
- Look, I'm sorry I yelled.

19:59.966 --> 20:01.534
It's been a rough
several months for me

20:01.534 --> 20:03.636
and I think I'm starting
to lose it a bit.

20:05.004 --> 20:06.138
I apologize.

20:07.307 --> 20:09.008
You sure I can't just
give you some money

20:09.041 --> 20:10.577
and maybe you can finish early?

20:12.579 --> 20:14.914
- I can't do it, but
I finished fast, I go.

20:14.981 --> 20:19.986
Okay?

20:24.424 --> 20:27.327
(machine whirring)

20:29.562 --> 20:32.231
(ominous music)

20:48.281 --> 20:51.117
(Javier screaming)

20:57.390 --> 21:00.226
(machine whirring)

21:05.765 --> 21:08.301
- I feel like such
a giant douche bag.

21:08.368 --> 21:10.269
- I mean, yeah.

21:11.438 --> 21:13.072
- That's the last
thing that guy needed.

21:13.072 --> 21:16.075
Was some crazy girl yelling
at him for doing his job.

21:16.108 --> 21:18.611
I probably sound no better
than some racist asshole.

21:18.611 --> 21:20.747
Oh!

21:20.747 --> 21:23.049
- Oh, it's not that bad.

21:23.049 --> 21:24.984
Those things are super
loud and annoying.

21:24.984 --> 21:27.454
Especially when you're
tired with a headache.

21:27.454 --> 21:29.556
I'm sure you're not the first
person to say something.

21:29.589 --> 21:32.091
I can't tell you how many
times I wanted to myself.

21:34.627 --> 21:35.428
- It's just,

21:36.796 --> 21:37.764
then I...

21:42.435 --> 21:43.235
- What?

21:46.005 --> 21:47.840
- Nevermind, nothing.

21:47.840 --> 21:48.641
Not important.

21:49.809 --> 21:51.310
- [Roberta] You sure?

21:51.310 --> 21:52.912
- Yes.

21:52.912 --> 21:53.746
What's for dinner?

21:54.914 --> 21:58.818
- I was thinking
tacos then margaritas.

21:58.818 --> 22:00.286
- Wait, really?

22:00.319 --> 22:02.789
Or are you making
fun of me still?

22:02.789 --> 22:03.590
- A little bit of both.

22:03.590 --> 22:04.424
- Hey!

22:05.592 --> 22:06.926
- Wait, but you
like tacos, right?

22:06.959 --> 22:08.194
- Of course I like tacos.

22:08.194 --> 22:10.863
I just feel weird saying
like, "Yay tacos!"

22:10.930 --> 22:12.164
given what just happened.

22:12.164 --> 22:13.800
(Roberta chuckles)

22:13.833 --> 22:15.668
- It's actually more
ignorant for you

22:15.668 --> 22:17.837
to assume that he was Mexican.

22:17.837 --> 22:20.006
He could have been from El
Salvador for all you know.

22:20.006 --> 22:21.508
- Oh, geez, you're right.

22:21.541 --> 22:22.675
(Liz groans)

22:22.675 --> 22:25.678
- Come on, I'm totally kidding.

22:28.381 --> 22:30.550
- [Liz] Why do I suck so bad?

22:30.617 --> 22:32.218
- You don't.

22:32.218 --> 22:33.853
You actually suck good.

22:35.822 --> 22:37.457
- How would you know?

22:37.457 --> 22:38.791
- I can just imagine.

22:43.463 --> 22:44.330
- Thank you.

22:45.297 --> 22:46.666
Thank you for being awesome.

22:48.468 --> 22:49.736
- I honestly can't help it.

22:52.539 --> 22:54.173
- [Liz] Brody!

22:54.206 --> 22:56.075
- Hey, where are you going?

22:56.075 --> 22:57.644
- My dog is more humble than you

22:57.677 --> 22:59.245
and he's totally
full of himself.

23:03.182 --> 23:05.852
(ominous music)

23:09.522 --> 23:12.358
(heavy breathing)

23:18.330 --> 23:19.932
Why won't you leave me alone!

23:26.739 --> 23:28.841
I know you're out here
you son of a bitch.

23:32.244 --> 23:36.182
Where are you?

23:36.182 --> 23:38.918
(dramatic music)

23:40.853 --> 23:43.355
(Liz screams)

23:53.566 --> 23:55.735
Wake up, wake up, wake up!

23:55.768 --> 23:57.103
Wake up, wake up!

23:58.104 --> 24:00.540
(Liz screams)

24:06.646 --> 24:09.148
(Brody barks)

24:25.598 --> 24:28.267
(clock chiming)

24:51.591 --> 24:54.594
(suspenseful music)

25:17.850 --> 25:20.620
(walls rumbling)

25:35.034 --> 25:37.536
(door creaks)

25:43.409 --> 25:45.712
(Liz screams)

25:45.712 --> 25:48.547
(heavy breathing)

26:07.399 --> 26:09.902
(door creaks)

26:19.178 --> 26:20.012
Wow.

26:21.113 --> 26:22.949
Hold it together, Liz.

26:23.950 --> 26:25.351
Hold it together.

26:29.889 --> 26:32.558
(water running)

26:36.763 --> 26:39.298
(Liz chuckles)

26:43.535 --> 26:48.540
(dramatic music)
(glass shatters)

26:54.981 --> 26:56.215
- Hey, do you have any of that

26:56.248 --> 26:57.784
non-dairy vegan
coffee ice cream.

26:57.784 --> 26:58.885
I like in your fridge?

27:00.720 --> 27:02.421
You know that stuff that
you had that one time,

27:02.454 --> 27:05.557
the like only time you
ever made me dinner?

27:10.296 --> 27:11.130
Hello?

27:12.131 --> 27:15.601
Liz, what are you doing?

27:17.469 --> 27:19.338
Oh, hey Brody!

27:19.338 --> 27:21.140
What is up my guy?

27:21.140 --> 27:23.743
Oh yeah, I miss you too!

27:23.776 --> 27:24.944
You're so big.

27:27.313 --> 27:30.649
Liz, oh my God,
what is going on?

27:33.319 --> 27:35.454
I have no idea what's
going on over there,

27:35.487 --> 27:37.857
but you look ridiculous.

27:37.857 --> 27:39.692
This actually reminds
me of that one time

27:39.759 --> 27:41.427
that you snuck into my room

27:41.427 --> 27:44.163
and tried to jack my
scuba dive Barbie,

27:44.163 --> 27:47.099
and I totally caught you, but
you thought I didn't see you.

27:47.133 --> 27:51.838
So you like inch your
way through the door.

27:51.838 --> 27:53.439
And I was like, "Dude, why
are you jacking my settings?"

27:53.472 --> 27:56.342
And you're like, "I'm not
jacking your settings."

27:58.144 --> 28:01.647
Oh God, jacking my settings.

28:01.680 --> 28:04.150
What a stupid saying our
dad ingrained into us.

28:04.150 --> 28:07.453
I still say jacking
all the time.

28:08.721 --> 28:10.156
Okay Liz, enough.

28:10.189 --> 28:11.023
What is up?

28:15.494 --> 28:16.729
- You are dead.

28:22.368 --> 28:23.202
- Am I?

28:25.637 --> 28:28.640
(Payton laughing)

28:28.640 --> 28:30.509
I'm just messing
sis, of course I am.

28:30.542 --> 28:33.345
I'm dead as Daffy
in duck season.

28:33.345 --> 28:34.246
Or am I?

28:37.750 --> 28:41.253
- What, what are you
doing here, Payton?

28:41.253 --> 28:43.422
- Well I wanted to see you.

28:43.489 --> 28:46.525
I mean, you look like shit,
all that lack of sleep.

28:46.558 --> 28:47.726
- Thank you.

28:47.726 --> 28:49.561
- Hey, what are older
sisters for, huh?

28:51.697 --> 28:54.033
- I'm completely losing my mind.

28:54.066 --> 28:57.003
- This is true, but I do
have some good news for you.

28:57.003 --> 29:00.172
It turns out, I can help you.

29:00.206 --> 29:02.674
You just gotta
listen to me, okay?

29:02.674 --> 29:04.844
Come here, sit down.

29:04.844 --> 29:05.711
Let's have a Kiki.

29:25.531 --> 29:28.434
- [Liz] What's it
like to be dead?

29:28.434 --> 29:29.435
- Short answer,

29:30.402 --> 29:32.905
it sucks.

29:32.905 --> 29:35.074
It is so boring.

29:35.074 --> 29:37.476
And, there's this.

29:37.476 --> 29:40.379
(bone snaps)
(Payton grunts)

29:40.412 --> 29:42.281
This is supposed
be attached to me.

29:46.285 --> 29:47.653
Other than that
though, honestly,

29:47.719 --> 29:49.889
it's really not that
different from being alive.

29:51.290 --> 29:53.792
- I've completely lost my mind.

29:53.792 --> 29:55.661
- Most likely, yeah.

29:55.661 --> 29:57.329
But I have to tell you sis,

29:57.329 --> 30:00.166
this isn't going to
stop until you let go.

30:00.166 --> 30:01.000
- Let go?

30:02.634 --> 30:03.802
Of what?

30:03.836 --> 30:05.838
- Well you can start
with that chick.

30:05.905 --> 30:07.106
- Chick.

30:07.139 --> 30:08.407
You mean Roberta?

30:08.407 --> 30:12.011
- Mm-hm, yeah, she
is bad news bears.

30:12.011 --> 30:12.845
- Are you kidding?

30:12.845 --> 30:13.779
She's a godsend.

30:13.812 --> 30:14.646
- Whoa!

30:15.982 --> 30:17.449
No.

30:17.449 --> 30:19.986
Nope, cut that shit loose.

30:19.986 --> 30:20.819
- Okay.

30:23.322 --> 30:25.357
Let's say you're actually
here talking to me.

30:25.424 --> 30:26.658
- Let's.

30:26.658 --> 30:28.360
- And this isn't some
insane hallucination,

30:28.427 --> 30:30.329
which I'm pretty sure it is,

30:31.697 --> 30:33.499
what the hell are
you talking about?

30:40.272 --> 30:43.775
- Liz, I have something to say.

30:46.145 --> 30:46.979
I'm sorry.

30:48.680 --> 30:49.681
I'm sorry about Seth.

30:53.019 --> 30:57.023
I'm sorry I had
a thing with him.

30:57.056 --> 30:59.058
You knew didn't you?

30:59.058 --> 31:00.492
- I suspected.

31:00.526 --> 31:03.362
- [Payton] Then why
didn't you say something?

31:03.362 --> 31:05.164
- What was I supposed to say?

31:05.197 --> 31:06.832
- I don't know, anything!

31:06.832 --> 31:08.867
- Hey Payton, are you
banging my boyfriend?

31:08.867 --> 31:10.069
Something like that?

31:10.136 --> 31:11.904
- I didn't know, I
wanted to be wrong.

31:11.904 --> 31:13.372
I wanted it to go away.

31:16.408 --> 31:17.809
- Is that why you hesitated?

31:19.211 --> 31:20.479
- Huh?

31:20.512 --> 31:23.082
- That day on the water
I could have sworn

31:23.082 --> 31:25.184
you hesitated to pull
me into the boat.

31:26.652 --> 31:28.354
(tense music)

31:28.387 --> 31:29.555
- What?

31:29.555 --> 31:31.690
- It's okay sis, I get it.

31:31.690 --> 31:32.858
It was just a moment.

31:32.891 --> 31:34.226
- No, I would-

31:34.226 --> 31:36.062
- Just long enough
for it to get me.

31:37.063 --> 31:38.330
- Wait!

31:38.330 --> 31:39.098
I didn't!

31:41.100 --> 31:41.934
I didn't!

31:43.402 --> 31:44.203
I didn't!

31:49.041 --> 31:51.543
(Liz laughing)

31:55.047 --> 31:57.283
And then that was
it, she was gone.

31:57.283 --> 31:59.285
- Just, gone?

31:59.285 --> 32:00.086
- Yep.

32:01.253 --> 32:02.688
- Did you actually
see her vanish,

32:02.721 --> 32:05.557
or was she just
there then not there?

32:05.591 --> 32:06.758
- Do you mean if
I actually saw her

32:06.758 --> 32:08.427
disintegrate or something?

32:08.427 --> 32:09.695
- [Therapist] Well, whatever.

32:10.896 --> 32:14.600
- No, she was just
there, then not.

32:15.634 --> 32:17.469
- I always wondered about that.

32:17.469 --> 32:20.306
When people say that
they saw something

32:20.372 --> 32:21.773
vanish in front of their eyes.

32:21.773 --> 32:24.410
What that really looked like.

32:24.443 --> 32:25.777
It's never happened to me.

32:27.446 --> 32:28.280
- Okay.

32:29.781 --> 32:30.616
That's cool.

32:33.085 --> 32:35.754
- I didn't mean to distract
you with questions.

32:37.323 --> 32:38.224
Please continue.

32:39.125 --> 32:39.992
- [Liz] That's it.

32:41.660 --> 32:43.662
- What do you think she meant

32:43.729 --> 32:47.933
about Roberta being
"bad news bears"?

32:47.966 --> 32:48.967
- I have no idea.

32:49.901 --> 32:50.669
Zero.

32:52.171 --> 32:54.506
I would think she'd be happy
that there was someone there

32:54.506 --> 32:56.408
to comfort and take care of me.

32:57.343 --> 32:58.177
- Yeah.

32:58.177 --> 32:59.145
- Yeah, so I don't know.

32:59.145 --> 33:00.612
That's just all kinds of wrong.

33:02.081 --> 33:02.981
- [Therapist] Do
you wanna talk about

33:02.981 --> 33:04.950
what she said at the end?

33:04.983 --> 33:06.818
About the hesitation?

33:09.355 --> 33:11.923
- I don't think I hesitated.

33:11.957 --> 33:12.791
- Okay.

33:14.660 --> 33:16.995
- But I don't know.

33:18.797 --> 33:21.667
- Up til now your guilt
has been about being

33:21.667 --> 33:24.836
the only survivor, correct?

33:24.870 --> 33:25.704
- I guess.

33:27.473 --> 33:29.375
- [Therapist] Maybe
there's more to it.

33:31.777 --> 33:33.779
- You saying I did hesitate?

33:33.779 --> 33:34.613
- Not at all.

33:36.682 --> 33:38.850
But maybe you think you did?

33:40.186 --> 33:42.688
You said you told
Payton that you

33:42.688 --> 33:46.024
suspected something was
going on, but did you,

33:46.024 --> 33:47.459
or did you actually know?

33:49.195 --> 33:50.529
- I don't know, maybe.

33:51.697 --> 33:54.966
- Okay, we don't have
to talk about this.

33:56.202 --> 33:58.470
- I just wanna know
why Payton came to me.

33:59.705 --> 34:01.540
- Hallucinations have no logic.

34:03.509 --> 34:05.377
- Are you sure it
was a hallucination?

34:07.045 --> 34:09.548
(tense music)

34:14.386 --> 34:16.388
No, not today.

34:21.427 --> 34:22.828
- [Roberta] There you are.

34:22.861 --> 34:24.330
- Hi.

34:24.330 --> 34:26.165
- I was knocking out front.

34:26.165 --> 34:28.434
- Oh, sorry, I was
just back here.

34:30.102 --> 34:31.603
- Thinking about taking a swim?

34:31.603 --> 34:33.505
- No, not yet.

34:33.539 --> 34:34.506
- You sure?

34:34.506 --> 34:35.841
It could be fun.

34:35.874 --> 34:37.209
- I'm sure.

34:37.243 --> 34:38.210
Hey, you're early.

34:38.210 --> 34:39.878
Dinner's not ready yet.

34:39.911 --> 34:42.748
- Yeah, I got off
work on time for once.

34:42.748 --> 34:45.083
I was excited to see
what my girls made me.

34:45.083 --> 34:46.385
- Well don't get too excited.

34:46.385 --> 34:48.420
I basically know how
to make two things.

34:48.420 --> 34:49.921
Meatloaf and stir fry.

34:49.921 --> 34:50.956
- Ooh, yum.

34:51.857 --> 34:53.192
So, what we having?

34:53.225 --> 34:57.196
- I thought we'd have fish.
(slow paced music)

35:09.641 --> 35:10.476
- Mm, wow.

35:12.278 --> 35:13.111
Thank you, babe.

35:13.111 --> 35:14.280
That was really good.

35:14.313 --> 35:15.947
- Stop lying.

35:15.947 --> 35:16.915
- I'm not lying.

35:16.948 --> 35:18.150
- Yay!

35:18.150 --> 35:21.052
(Roberta chuckles)

35:26.892 --> 35:28.294
- How was your session today?

35:29.661 --> 35:30.662
- It was interesting.

35:32.464 --> 35:33.399
- [Roberta] How so?

35:35.801 --> 35:37.469
- I haven't really told you

35:37.469 --> 35:39.638
about that day
Payton and Seth died.

35:39.671 --> 35:40.472
Have I?

35:41.640 --> 35:42.641
- Not really.

35:44.142 --> 35:47.078
I just figured you weren't
ready to talk about the details.

35:48.113 --> 35:48.947
- I wasn't,

35:50.249 --> 35:51.250
but I am now.

35:53.685 --> 35:55.287
- Oh.

35:55.321 --> 35:56.422
Okay then.

35:56.422 --> 35:58.490
- But we need wine first.

35:58.490 --> 35:59.325
Lots of it.

36:00.659 --> 36:02.160
- [Roberta] I'm down for that.

36:04.796 --> 36:08.667
- Doctor said I was lucky I
didn't bleed out or lose my leg.

36:09.835 --> 36:11.102
- Fuck.

36:11.102 --> 36:12.604
- Peyton and Seth
weren't so lucky.

36:14.005 --> 36:14.840
- Wow.

36:16.842 --> 36:18.477
- Do you have any battle scars?

36:18.477 --> 36:20.612
- Um, well-

36:20.612 --> 36:22.113
- What am I saying,
of course you don't.

36:22.147 --> 36:23.482
You are perfect.

36:23.515 --> 36:25.217
- Far from it.

36:25.217 --> 36:28.620
Oh, look, check this out.

36:28.654 --> 36:30.155
- What am I looking at?

36:30.188 --> 36:32.524
- Bee sting, fourth grade.

36:32.524 --> 36:33.659
(both laugh)

36:33.692 --> 36:34.526
- Please.

36:35.394 --> 36:36.228
- I crack me up.

36:36.295 --> 36:38.063
- Oh, I know you do.

36:38.063 --> 36:39.398
- [Roberta] Cheers to that.

36:49.708 --> 36:52.311
- We were on our
scuba dive trip,

36:52.311 --> 36:53.579
I had just learned
and it was gonna

36:53.579 --> 36:55.881
be my first time
in the open ocean.

36:55.881 --> 36:58.684
I was nervous like
you wouldn't believe.

36:58.717 --> 37:00.552
The sea has always scared me.

37:00.552 --> 37:01.887
- Me too, I understand.

37:01.887 --> 37:04.256
- Yeah, the not knowing
what's under there.

37:04.323 --> 37:05.324
The power of it.

37:06.492 --> 37:08.059
You know, I was
always drawn to it.

37:10.161 --> 37:13.164
Anyway, so we're
there in the water.

37:13.164 --> 37:14.833
Our raft just a few meters away.

37:16.234 --> 37:19.571
I started to freak out
and swim back to the raft.

37:19.571 --> 37:20.906
I couldn't get
myself to dive under,

37:20.906 --> 37:22.508
even after all those lessons.

37:24.009 --> 37:25.344
I'm just about to climb in,

37:26.912 --> 37:28.380
Payton and Seth are of course

37:28.414 --> 37:30.416
yelling at me to come
back, but I didn't listen.

37:31.783 --> 37:33.852
At one point, I remember
turning around to face them

37:33.885 --> 37:35.554
one last time before going in,

37:37.088 --> 37:39.257
and there they were
looking so close.

37:41.126 --> 37:42.127
So intimate.

37:44.029 --> 37:46.565
I felt a shutter
of disappointment

37:48.700 --> 37:49.701
and disgust.

37:52.103 --> 37:54.105
I had suspected there was
something going on between them,

37:54.105 --> 37:56.608
but that's, that's when I knew.

37:56.608 --> 37:59.277
(tense music)

37:59.277 --> 38:02.247
I turned to get in and I
feel this pull on my leg.

38:05.784 --> 38:07.786
I can't explain
it, it jolted me.

38:10.456 --> 38:12.724
I reached down and feel
my leg has been torn.

38:14.960 --> 38:16.261
There's blood on my hand.

38:18.964 --> 38:22.300
I'm just about to scream when
there's this splashing sound

38:22.300 --> 38:25.437
and Seth is yelling "Shark,
get back to the raft."

38:25.471 --> 38:26.772
Payton, the screaming too.

38:29.140 --> 38:34.145
Seth is flailing in the
water, then whoosh, he's gone.

38:37.315 --> 38:38.316
Taken under.

38:40.151 --> 38:41.787
Just red water left behind.

38:45.657 --> 38:48.460
Payton is screaming,
"Get back to the raft."

38:48.460 --> 38:50.796
She starts swimming towards me.

38:50.796 --> 38:51.997
I don't know where I
found the strength,

38:51.997 --> 38:53.264
but I pull myself in.

38:54.766 --> 38:57.268
I look and see Peyton
swimming as fast as she can.

39:01.139 --> 39:03.709
I can see the shadow of
the shark behind her.

39:03.709 --> 39:04.943
It's not like in the movies

39:04.976 --> 39:07.145
where you see the
fin chasing her.

39:07.178 --> 39:08.013
No.

39:10.215 --> 39:11.450
It was deeper in the water,

39:11.483 --> 39:12.818
but from my view,
I could see it.

39:13.952 --> 39:15.487
I yell at her to hurry.

39:15.521 --> 39:17.789
She's almost to the
raft, she reaches for me,

39:17.789 --> 39:19.891
I reach for her and-

39:19.891 --> 39:20.726
- [Payton] Help!

39:20.726 --> 39:22.394
Help please!

39:22.461 --> 39:23.462
- She's taken under.

39:26.197 --> 39:28.033
Swift and silent, like nothing.

39:29.868 --> 39:33.539
I don't know if it
was one shark or many.

39:33.539 --> 39:36.708
I'm guessing many, because
that would make more sense.

39:41.179 --> 39:44.983
At this point, it's just
me alone in the raft,

39:46.885 --> 39:47.686
in shock

39:49.220 --> 39:50.055
and bleeding.

39:54.760 --> 39:55.561
- Wow.

39:56.562 --> 39:59.030
I have no idea what to say.

40:00.265 --> 40:02.434
I can't even imagine.

40:02.501 --> 40:06.872
- Yeah, luckily a yacht
came by to save me.

40:06.905 --> 40:09.107
I mean, that was damn lucky.

40:09.107 --> 40:10.876
- Someone was watching over you.

40:10.909 --> 40:13.211
- Oh, I don't believe
in that bullshit.

40:13.211 --> 40:14.012
- It's okay.

40:15.180 --> 40:16.047
You don't have to.

40:17.716 --> 40:18.917
- The thing is I think I,

40:24.389 --> 40:28.426
hesitated when I reached
to help Payton out.

40:32.030 --> 40:32.864
I think I,

40:36.602 --> 40:38.470
I think I wanted the
shark to get her.

40:39.471 --> 40:42.307
- No, that couldn't be true.

40:44.610 --> 40:45.777
- I don't know.

40:48.446 --> 40:50.782
