45:48.079 --> 45:49.680
- Huh?

45:49.680 --> 45:50.515
- Nevermind.

45:51.716 --> 45:55.586
So I hear someone almost
got laid last night.

45:55.586 --> 45:57.555
- That's none of your business.

45:57.588 --> 46:00.591
- Well Seth already told
me all about it, so.

46:00.591 --> 46:01.626
- You guys talk?

46:01.626 --> 46:03.294
- Oh yeah, all the time.

46:05.630 --> 46:08.133
It's not like there's much
else to do around here.

46:09.134 --> 46:10.301
Are you sure you
don't have like,

46:10.368 --> 46:12.971
just something that
I can munch on?

46:12.971 --> 46:13.972
- Can you even eat?

46:13.972 --> 46:14.806
- Yeah.

46:16.041 --> 46:18.376
Well, no, but yeah.

46:23.781 --> 46:27.452
Ooh yes, that is what
I'm talking about.

46:28.619 --> 46:29.454
Come on.

46:31.222 --> 46:32.924
- Do you mind if I pour
myself some coffee?

46:32.958 --> 46:35.560
- Not at all, but do me a
favor and pass those over.

46:38.296 --> 46:39.130
Hey-o!

46:44.569 --> 46:47.939
(Payton groans)

46:47.973 --> 46:49.607
- You look like shit, Payton.

46:50.608 --> 46:51.609
- You stole my line.

46:52.743 --> 46:55.413
And yeah, yeah, I don't
look so hot, I know.

46:56.814 --> 46:59.817
God, remember how flawless
my skin was in life?

46:59.817 --> 47:01.086
- I do.

47:01.119 --> 47:02.954
I hated you for it.

47:02.954 --> 47:03.788
- Oh, I know.

47:03.821 --> 47:05.256
- My zits had zits,

47:05.256 --> 47:07.993
meanwhile, your skin was smooth
as shit from a duck's ass.

47:07.993 --> 47:09.160
(Payton laughs)

47:09.194 --> 47:11.462
- Nice, and accurate.

47:11.496 --> 47:14.099
- All the boys and
the girls actually

47:14.099 --> 47:17.335
wanted to touch my sister's
smooth, perfect skin.

47:17.335 --> 47:21.006
- Oh, stop hating sis.

47:21.006 --> 47:23.141
Plus, look at me now.

47:24.675 --> 47:27.045
- It's actually kind of
good to see you, Payton.

47:27.045 --> 47:29.214
Even if you look
like puked up sushi.

47:30.681 --> 47:32.283
- Thank you.

47:32.317 --> 47:34.152
- So, what's up?

47:37.188 --> 47:40.458
(Payton clears throat)

47:44.695 --> 47:47.198
- Ugh, plain black coffee.

47:47.198 --> 47:48.733
Ugh.

47:48.733 --> 47:49.901
- You want water?

47:49.968 --> 47:51.569
- No, I'm good.

47:51.569 --> 47:55.406
Now, you don't seem
to be getting it.

47:55.406 --> 47:56.908
- Sure, I do.

47:56.975 --> 47:58.709
You and Seth are undead,

47:58.709 --> 48:01.980
and I need to get rid of
Roberta for some reason.

48:02.880 --> 48:05.984
- Yeah, that's right.

48:05.984 --> 48:07.418
- Why?

48:07.418 --> 48:10.321
- [Payton] You just have
to, she's holding you back.

48:10.355 --> 48:11.256
- From what?

48:11.256 --> 48:14.259
- Liz, listen to me.

48:14.259 --> 48:17.762
If you don't, Seth and
I will never go away

48:17.762 --> 48:20.431
and you will be
cursed to see us rot.

48:20.431 --> 48:22.667
- I don't understand
any of this.

48:22.700 --> 48:25.570
- [Payton] You don't have to,
you just have to believe me.

48:27.772 --> 48:31.542
- So breaking up with
her will change that?

48:31.576 --> 48:33.211
- I didn't say
break up with her.

48:34.212 --> 48:36.214
I said, get rid of her.

48:36.247 --> 48:38.749
(ominous music)

48:38.749 --> 48:41.886
- Wait a minute, you don't mean-

48:41.919 --> 48:44.555
(ear splashes)

48:44.555 --> 48:45.390
- Shit.

48:46.924 --> 48:48.093
(Liz gags)

48:48.093 --> 48:48.926
Sorry.

48:50.528 --> 48:53.898
Hey, hey, hey, it's okay.

48:53.931 --> 48:55.066
It's all good.

48:55.066 --> 48:56.767
No worries, okay.

48:56.767 --> 48:58.603
See, all good.

48:59.704 --> 49:00.871
(Liz gags)

49:00.905 --> 49:02.907
Oh, come on sis, stop
being so dramatic,

49:02.907 --> 49:04.075
it wasn't all that.

49:04.075 --> 49:06.311
(Liz gags)

49:13.784 --> 49:16.421
- That was truly the most
disgusting thing I've ever seen.

49:16.454 --> 49:17.989
- I admit, it was not tight.

49:19.624 --> 49:20.758
So are you good?

49:20.791 --> 49:22.627
(Liz gags)

49:22.627 --> 49:23.561
- I'm good.

49:25.963 --> 49:29.967
- So I take it you
don't want this coffee?

49:32.103 --> 49:32.937
Cool.

49:34.305 --> 49:38.343
(Payton clears throat)

49:38.409 --> 49:40.645
(Liz gags)

49:44.449 --> 49:47.252
All right sis, I gotta head,

49:48.686 --> 49:50.188
but remember what I said, okay.

49:50.255 --> 49:52.157
- I don't even
know what you said.

49:52.157 --> 49:53.324
- Yeah, you do.

49:53.358 --> 49:55.026
- I still don't understand why.

49:56.194 --> 49:58.429
- Get rid of her!
(dramatic music)

50:01.966 --> 50:04.335
(tense music)

50:04.335 --> 50:06.537
- [Therapist] Wow, that's
some intense stuff.

50:08.173 --> 50:09.107
- Yeah.

50:09.140 --> 50:10.175
- What do you think it means?

50:11.342 --> 50:13.778
- Isn't that what you
are supposed to tell me?

50:13.811 --> 50:15.213
- Not necessarily.

50:15.213 --> 50:18.849
- I love that answer
that's not an answer.

50:19.950 --> 50:21.119
- That's what we do.

50:22.487 --> 50:25.690
In all seriousness, I'm
supposed to help you

50:25.690 --> 50:29.227
decipher what it means,
not tell you what it means.

50:30.328 --> 50:32.830
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

50:32.830 --> 50:34.832
- I know that this is tough.

50:34.832 --> 50:37.168
I know that you want
definitive answers.

50:38.403 --> 50:40.538
Unfortunately, I can't
provide you with that,

50:41.572 --> 50:43.408
but can I offer a suggestion?

50:45.410 --> 50:49.013
I know that we discussed
swimming in the pool

50:50.648 --> 50:53.684
as a way to face your fear
of being an actual water,

50:53.718 --> 50:55.553
with Roberta there
to support you.

50:55.553 --> 50:56.487
- Yeah.

50:57.588 --> 50:59.157
I don't think-

50:59.190 --> 51:03.494
- I think that it would be a
first step to another level.

51:04.229 --> 51:04.829
Just something to try.

51:06.564 --> 51:07.998
- I'm not ready for that yet.

51:09.767 --> 51:11.102
- Will you consider it?

51:11.169 --> 51:14.172
- Yeah, I'll consider
it, but I won't do it.

51:15.573 --> 51:18.343
- Well then that's not really
considering it, is it Liz?

51:20.845 --> 51:22.513
- I don't give a
flying rat's ass.

51:22.513 --> 51:25.015
There's no way I'm ready
to get into a pool.

51:25.015 --> 51:27.685
Nuh-uh, no way, nope.

51:27.718 --> 51:29.254
- Come on Liz.

51:29.254 --> 51:31.522
Just put your feet in,
I'll hold your hands.

51:31.556 --> 51:32.757
- I'm good.

51:32.757 --> 51:34.559
This is as close to the
pool as I like to get.

51:34.592 --> 51:37.262
- Oh, come on, for me?

51:37.262 --> 51:39.764
- Don't try that, it
might actually work.

51:39.764 --> 51:41.266
- That's what I'm counting on!

51:45.403 --> 51:46.704
Yay!

51:46.704 --> 51:47.872
- Just give me a minute.

51:47.872 --> 51:49.106
Don't try anything!

51:49.106 --> 51:50.908
- I won't, I wouldn't dare.

51:50.941 --> 51:51.809
Take your time.

51:54.645 --> 51:56.547
Oh, you're doing so good baby!

51:56.581 --> 51:59.584
- Don't do that child,
baby encouraging talk.

51:59.617 --> 52:00.418
I'll just bail.

52:00.418 --> 52:02.086
- Okay, okay, I'm sorry.

52:02.119 --> 52:03.821
Me shush, shush.

52:07.958 --> 52:10.461
(tense music)

52:15.666 --> 52:19.003
(ominous music)

52:19.003 --> 52:19.837
What?

52:21.806 --> 52:23.241
(Liz screams)
(water splashing)

52:23.241 --> 52:24.809
- Don't let go!
(Roberta screams)

52:24.809 --> 52:25.643
Roberta!

52:29.146 --> 52:31.015
(ominous music)

52:31.081 --> 52:32.417
- You okay?

52:32.417 --> 52:33.251
Did you trip?

52:37.455 --> 52:38.456
- I can't.

52:40.291 --> 52:41.626
I can't.

52:41.626 --> 52:42.427
- God.

52:44.429 --> 52:46.030
- I can't, I'm sorry.

52:46.931 --> 52:48.499
- Oh, it's okay.

52:48.499 --> 52:49.767
It's okay.

52:49.800 --> 52:50.601
It's okay.

52:51.936 --> 52:52.703
It's okay.

52:55.440 --> 52:58.042
(ominous music)

53:18.028 --> 53:18.863
- Yes, I know.

53:19.830 --> 53:22.233
I can try more meditation maybe.

53:22.233 --> 53:24.469
- [Therapist] That doesn't
seem to be working for you.

53:25.870 --> 53:28.906
- Yeah, but I haven't been
putting all my focus onto it.

53:28.973 --> 53:29.907
I've been lazy.

53:31.075 --> 53:32.843
Also, I haven't been exercising.

53:35.380 --> 53:36.814
Let me try again.

53:36.814 --> 53:39.216
If there's no progress,

53:39.216 --> 53:43.020
if it gets worse, then
I'll take something, fair?

53:45.356 --> 53:46.324
- [Therapist] Fair.

53:53.564 --> 53:54.399
- Ohm.

53:56.100 --> 53:59.203
Oh my God, this is
never going to work.

53:59.236 --> 54:00.037
Ohm.

54:01.372 --> 54:03.207
- Payton, what do you want?

54:03.240 --> 54:04.675
Why are you doing this?

54:04.675 --> 54:07.678
- Told ya, you
gotta cut her loose.

54:07.678 --> 54:09.914
Gotta cut all this shit loose.

54:09.914 --> 54:11.716
Otherwise it's just
gonna get worse.

54:14.952 --> 54:17.788
(water splashing)

54:28.399 --> 54:31.068
(ominous music)

54:33.938 --> 54:35.540
- Want some fruit?

54:35.573 --> 54:36.574
It's really ripe.

54:38.108 --> 54:38.943
- No, thank you.

54:42.913 --> 54:45.483
- Hey, at work today,
Brendan was telling me

54:45.483 --> 54:48.653
this crazy gossip about
my coworker, Josh,

54:48.719 --> 54:50.220
who I was telling you about.

54:50.254 --> 54:53.424
The one who's always saying
inappropriate things.

54:53.458 --> 54:56.661
So apparently he tells
my boss that he thinks

54:56.661 --> 54:59.997
his manness is holding
him back at the office.

55:00.064 --> 55:02.433
(Roberta laughs)

55:02.467 --> 55:05.403
Like, isn't that hilarious?

55:05.403 --> 55:07.505
God, I just want that
guy to get a haircut.

55:08.406 --> 55:10.074
(Liz chuckles)

55:10.107 --> 55:11.008
You ready to eat?

55:15.480 --> 55:18.516
(dramatic music)

55:18.516 --> 55:21.586
Hey, I get it if
you don't like it,

55:21.619 --> 55:24.021
but you can be a
little nicer though.

55:25.990 --> 55:27.458
- I know, I'm sorry.

55:28.926 --> 55:32.930
It looks great, I'm just,
totally losing my mind.

55:34.331 --> 55:35.766
- Don't say that.

55:35.766 --> 55:36.767
No, you're not.

55:38.836 --> 55:40.004
- I really think I am.

55:44.041 --> 55:48.278
- Look, I believe you can
beat this and get better.

55:49.447 --> 55:53.017
But if you give up,
there's no hope.

55:53.017 --> 55:56.020
And I'm sorry to be blunt
like this, but it's true.

55:56.053 --> 55:57.488
There's no hope.

55:58.689 --> 56:00.725
I've lost family
to mental illness.

56:00.791 --> 56:02.460
I can recognize the signs.

56:03.528 --> 56:07.532
But Liz, I believe in you.

56:07.532 --> 56:09.534
I know you have what it takes

56:09.534 --> 56:11.201
to conquer this and get better.

56:12.369 --> 56:14.905
But that doesn't mean
jack if you don't.

56:17.408 --> 56:22.413
Now, do you believe it?
(slow paced music)

56:22.880 --> 56:23.481
Say it.

56:25.082 --> 56:25.916
- I believe it.

56:27.518 --> 56:28.686
- [Roberta] Believe what?

56:31.656 --> 56:33.323
- That I can conquer this thing.

56:40.598 --> 56:42.066
- You're God damn right you can.

56:43.734 --> 56:45.069
Now who's my tough bitch?

56:47.237 --> 56:49.206
- I'm your tough bitch.

56:49.239 --> 56:50.074
- Hell yeah.

56:53.177 --> 56:56.280
(Roberta sighs)

56:56.280 --> 56:57.181
Now eat your food.

57:04.354 --> 57:07.024
(ominous music)

57:32.950 --> 57:35.653
(dramatic music)

57:51.435 --> 57:52.970
- Why?

57:52.970 --> 57:55.573
- None of us can go
anywhere until you do it.

57:55.606 --> 57:56.774
It's just the way it is.

57:57.975 --> 58:00.310
- Why can't I just
break up with her?

58:00.310 --> 58:02.580
- Yeah, go ahead and
try, it's not gonna work.

58:03.914 --> 58:04.815
- So you'll let me?

58:06.150 --> 58:07.585
You'll let me try that first?

58:08.986 --> 58:11.288
If I can get rid of her that
way, then it will be okay?

58:15.993 --> 58:18.796
- Sure, you have tonight.

58:18.829 --> 58:21.265
- Otherwise we're
gonna do it for you.

58:21.265 --> 58:22.099
- Have fun.

58:23.834 --> 58:26.871
(tense solemn music)

58:29.807 --> 58:31.041
- It's okay, Brody.

58:32.843 --> 58:34.712
Your Mama's not
full-blown psycho yet.

58:37.848 --> 58:39.116
- I don't understand.

58:40.685 --> 58:42.319
- I just think
it's best for now.

58:43.453 --> 58:45.122
I'm not handling
all this super well,

58:45.122 --> 58:48.659
and it's not fair to you
to have to take care of me.

58:48.693 --> 58:50.895
- But I like taking care of you.

58:50.895 --> 58:52.663
- That's sweet, but I don't.

58:53.798 --> 58:56.466
I feel useless and weak.

58:56.500 --> 58:58.335
I need to prove to myself
that I can face this

58:58.368 --> 58:59.536
and get over this alone.

59:00.905 --> 59:02.907
- I can respect that,

59:02.907 --> 59:05.175
but I think it's
a terrible idea.

59:05.209 --> 59:06.143
- Of course you do.

59:07.544 --> 59:09.246
- [Roberta] What does that mean?

59:09.313 --> 59:11.015
- It means you want
to be the hero.

59:12.249 --> 59:13.651
You probably liked me so much

59:13.684 --> 59:16.353
because you love the
idea of saving me.

59:16.353 --> 59:18.022
- That's not true.

59:18.055 --> 59:19.156
- Like, hell it isn't.

59:20.557 --> 59:22.727
I'm willing to bet that when
I finally do feel better,

59:22.727 --> 59:23.894
you'll lose interest.

59:25.362 --> 59:27.231
You'll get bored and want
to move on to the next

59:27.231 --> 59:29.366
damsel in distress
that you can find.

59:29.399 --> 59:31.001
- [Roberta] Liz, please.

59:31.001 --> 59:32.502
That can't be further
from the truth.

59:32.536 --> 59:35.039
- Well, I don't need
or want a savior.

59:35.039 --> 59:37.174
I survived the attack.
I can survive this.

59:37.174 --> 59:38.909
- I know you can.

59:38.909 --> 59:39.877
I'm rooting for you.

59:39.910 --> 59:41.445
- Okay, great, so we agree.

59:41.445 --> 59:43.580
So know please, let
me have my space.

59:46.283 --> 59:47.852
- Liz, what's going on?

59:47.885 --> 59:49.053
- Oh, for the love of Christ.

59:49.053 --> 59:50.454
There goes that
therapist talk again.

59:50.454 --> 59:53.357
I already have one therapist,
I don't need another.

59:53.390 --> 59:55.559
- Don't do this.

59:55.592 --> 59:56.426
I love you.

1:00:02.566 --> 1:00:03.734
(tense solemn music)

1:00:03.734 --> 1:00:06.570
- Well, I don't love you.

1:00:08.238 --> 1:00:09.239
Now please get out.

